  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TNT4">
<l>intiraṟkum piramaṟkum mutalvaṉ ṟaṉṉai</l>
<l>yirunilaṅkāl tīnīrviṇ pūta maintāy</l>
<l>centiṟatta tamiḻōcai vaṭacol lākit</l>
<l>ticaināṉku māyttiṅkaḷ ñāyi ṟāki</l>
<l>antarattil tēvarkku maṟiya lākā</l>
<l>vantaṇaṉai yantaṇarmāṭ ṭanti vaitta</l>
<l>mantirattai mantirattāl maṟavā teṉṟum</l>
<l>vāḻutiyēl vāḻalām maṭaneñ cammē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The Primal [Lord] for Indra and Brahma, the Brahman</l>
<l rend="indent">who is inconceivable [even] for the gods in heaven,</l>
<l>Being the vast earth, wind, fire, water, the heavens, [and] the five senses,</l>
<l rend="indent">being the fine, elegant sound of Tamil [and] northern words,</l>
<l>Being the four quarters, being the sun and moon,</l>
<l rend="indent">[he who is] the mantra kept [in] the Brahmins’ twilight prayers -</l>
<l>If you always praise [him] with [this] mantra, not forgetting [a word],</l>
<l rend="indent">we can prosper, simple heart.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
